# Web Scraping Project

## Introduction

This Node.js script is designed to scrape data from a specific website - [https://www.tanzapages.com](https://www.tanzapages.com) - with the provided parameters.

## Usage

### 1. Installation

Make sure you have Node.js installed on your machine. Additionally, install the required libraries using the following command:

```bash
npm install axios cheerio
```

### 2. Script Configuration
Open the script and modify the following parameters according to your requirements:

url: The base URL of the website you want to scrape (e.g., https://www.tanzapages.com/location/Dar_Es_Salaam/{page}).
pages_limit: The number of pages to scrape. Set it to the desired limit (e.g., 10).
items_limit_per_page: The maximum number of items to scrape per page (e.g., 20).
parent_selector: The CSS selector for the parent element holding the entire list (e.g., '.xyz' or '#xyz').
element_selectors: An array of CSS selectors representing individual item data within the parent element.
save_format: Defines how you want your data saved. Available options are 'csv' or 'json'.
### 3. Run the Script
Execute the script using the following command:

```bash
node server.js
```
### 4. Output
The scraped data will be saved in either CSV or JSON format based on your specified preference.

CSV: The data will be saved in a file named scraped_data.csv.
JSON: The data will be saved in a file named scraped_data.json.
Disclaimer
Ensure that you have the legal right to scrape data from the specified website and adhere to their terms of service.

